				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is a combat spell, not just an excape spell. This spell is awesome in combination with the lvl 4 spell color flux. I have been using this VERY successfully chain casting with color flux in S Karana against the aviaks. First I cast tashani on any of the birds that con mid blue(rooks and harriers) or higher. Next I run into the middle of the group of Aviaks(yes, getting beat on a bit). I cast color shift and color flux as fast as I can in a chain cast on myself and the intire mob is constantly stunned though out the entire battle. I was doing this in a full group that had two clerics and they never had to cast heal spells because the aviaks were always stunned and could never attack us. Take note though that even though it worked on Harrier Aviaks that conned yellow or red to me, it did not work on Avocet Aviaks that conned red and I believe were about 5 lvls higher than me. Oh, make sure there aren't any gaurds around when using this strategy in other zones as it is an AE (area effect) spell!<BR>
